pan class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">a test taken by British primary school children to check their progress in subjects of the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/nct\" title=\"National Curriculum definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">National Curriculum</span></a>. Tests are taken at the ages of 7 and 11. They are often referred to by their old name: <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/sat_2#sat_sng_2\" title=\"SAT definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">SAT</span></a> (Standard Assessment Tasks).</span></span>    \n</li></ol><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/national-curriculum-test\">National Curriculum Test</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["the National Crime Agency","the national curriculum noun","National Curriculum Test noun","the National Cycle Network","national debt noun"]},{"name":"résumé","pos":"noun","content":"<div class=\"entry\" sum=\"559\" hclass=\"entry\" htag=\"section\" id=\"resume_2\" hlength=\"2\" sk=\"resume: :5\" idm_id=\"000050048\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"resume_topg_2\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" htag=\"h1\" id=\"resume_h_2\" hclass=\"headword\">résumé</h1> <span class=\"pos\" hclass=\"pos\" htag=\"span\">noun</span><span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" wd=\"résumé\" hclass=\"phons_br\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"br\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/r/res/resum/resume_1_gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/r/res/resum/resume_1_gb_1.ogg\" title=\"résumé pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\"