es.com/definition/english/nct\" title=\"National Curriculum definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">National Curriculum</span></a>. Tests are taken at the ages of 7 and 11. They are often referred to by their old name: <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/sat_2#sat_sng_2\" title=\"SAT definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">SAT</span></a> (Standard Assessment Tasks).</span></span>    \n</li></ol><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/national-curriculum-test\">National Curriculum Test</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["the National Crime Agency","the national curriculum noun","National Curriculum Test noun","the National Cycle Network","national debt noun"]}]]